    {
      "name": "A new tariff comes into force from 1st January, 1888, under which all export duties and tonnage dues are abolished, the import duty on tobacco is reduced to 4d. per lb., and the following new import duties are imposed; lumber, 8s. per 100 ft.; oils, not kerosine, 6d. per gall.; hardware, 8s. per cwt.; salt, 3s. per ton; raw sugar 5s. per cwt.; ditto, refined 10s. per cwt.; claret 1s. per gall. (instead of 6d.); and 5 per cent. ad valorem on all other goods imported.",
